ratings.comment: Materials covered in this course are pretty straight forward and not too difficult to understand. Lots of readings assigned, most of which can be skimmed for the main idea. The professor uses TopHat so attendance is graded. There is also a pretty time consuming group project, but is is graded fairly. Exams are pretty easy and fair.

Prof. Toomarian was great at teaching this subject! She has so much knowledge about educational neuroscience and inspires me each class, even though it is an 8am lecture. As a student you can expect to read assigned articles each week, complete 3 midterms, and work in a group project in which you submit a research paper at the end of the semester.
